subSubSection.paragraph:
3.2 tetro lucente
: Refers to the ability to produce a dim light or glow. Rolander noted that the barn where the frogs were calling seemed as if illuminated by a yellow foxfire (“... horreum idem forte intravi, quod crepitantibus Ranis, quasi igne flavescente fatuo, illustrabatur... ”), and the glow was purportedly produced by the frogs “...as they alternately open and close their mouths to croak...” (
Boie 1827
;
Hansen 2008
).

